Preheat your oven to 200°C. Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Soak the
@bamboo skewers{4} in cold water to prevent them burning. Trim the
@courgette{3/4}(trimmed), then quarter lengthways. Cut widthways into
2cm pieces. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Roughly chop the
@flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Put the @couscous{120} in a #bowl{}. Pour the @water{240%ml} and half the
@chicken stock paste{20%g} into the bowl, cover tightly with #cling film{}
or a lid and leave to the side for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pop the @panko breadcrumbs{10%g} into a #medium bowl{}. Add the
@water for breadcrumbs{2%tbsp}, half the @ground cumin{1%tsp}, half the
@mild paprika{1%tsp} and season with salt and pepper. Add the
@British beef mince{240%g}. Mix with your hands until combined and shape into
2 sausage shapes per person. Flatten to make koftas and thread a skewer into
each one. Pop onto a #large baking tray{} and bake on the top shelf of your
oven until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The
> koftas are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). When hot, add the courgette and
cook until charred, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn only every couple of mins -
this will result in the courgette picking up some nice colour. Once cooked,
season with salt and pepper, then transfer the courgette to a bowl.

Once the courgette is charred, pop the pan back on medium heat with a drizzle
of oil. Add the remaining cumin, paprika and chicken stock paste, @tomato
puree{60%g}, @water for the sauce{150%ml}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and half the
remaining tomatoes. Bring to the boil. Reduce the heat and simmer until
slightly thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}, then stir in the charred courgettes.

Once the couscous is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{}. Add the remaining
tomatoes and half the chopped parsley, then season to taste. Stir together,
then divide the couscous among your plates. Top with the veg and 2 koftas
per person. Sprinkle on the remaining parsley. Enjoy!